subSubSection.paragraph:
Female
(
paralectotype
, 
Figs. 1f–h
): in general is similar to the male, but there is a strong sexual dimorphism evidenced by: 
(1)
mesosoma relatively wider; 
(2)
metasoma slightly less robust; 
(3)
pedipalp chela oval and more slender; 
(4)
pedipalp fingers with basal lobe/ notch combination less developed; 
(5)
genital papillae absent; 
(6)
pectines with teeth proportionally smaller; 
(6)
sternite V with smooth patch slightly smaller and less bulky.
